\par }{\f2\fs24\cgrid0 \\-----------------\\
\par |Starting The Game|==========================================>
\par /-----------------/}{\f2\cgrid0 
\par 
\par -There are three ways to start the game.
\par  : Choosing 'New' from the 'File' Menu
\par  : Clicking the 'Go' button
\par  : Pressing the space bar or enter
\par 
\par -There are also three ways to bypass the losing animation
\par  : Left click the window
\par  : Clicking the 'Go' button
\par  : Pressing the space bar or enter
\par 
\par }{\f2\fs24\cgrid0 \\----------------\\
\par |Playing The Game|===========================================>
\par /----------------/}{\f2\cgrid0 
\par 
\par }{\f2\fs24\ul\cgrid0 *BASIC IDEA*}{\f2\cgrid0 
\par  Mark\\Disable all the bombs on the board before time runs out to move
\par  on to the next level.
\par  
\par }{\f2\fs24\ul\cgrid0 *REVEAL SQUARES*}{\f2\cgrid0 
\par }{\b\f2\cgrid0 -What}{\f2\cgrid0 
\par  :Reveal the board until an intelligent decision can be made on where
\par   the bombs are possibly located.  
\par 
\par }{\b\f2\cgrid0 -HowTo:}{\f2\cgrid0 
\par :Left click to reveal squares.
\par :They will only reveal on release of button, to allow user to hop 
\par  to different squares while still holding.
\par 
\par }{\b\f2\cgrid0 -Outcome}{\f2\cgrid0 
\par :Upon revealing a square there will either be a number, nothing, or a bomb.
\par  >Nothing : No bomb, will open board till a bomb is detected
\par  >Number  : The number of bombs are present in the adjacent squares
\par  >Bomb    : Sorry pal your dead. Try again
\par 
\par :Depending on the numbers you will see, make decisions on where bombs could 
\par  be and mark those squares.  
\par 
\par }{\f2\fs24\ul\cgrid0 *MARK SQUARES*}{\f2\cgrid0 
\par }{\b\f2\cgrid0 -What}{\f2\cgrid0 
\par :Marking where you think a bomb is placed.
\par 
\par }{\b\f2\cgrid0 -HowTo}{\f2\cgrid0 
\par :Right click to mark a bomb.
\par :Right click a marked square to unmark it.
\par  
\par }{\b\f2\cgrid0 -Outcome}{\f2\cgrid0 
\par :If all bombs are marked, you will advance to the next level automatically.
\par :If all marks are used but you don't advance then at least one of your 
\par  marks is wrong.
\par 
\par }{\f2\fs24\ul\cgrid0 *AUTO-OPEN* }{\f2\cgrid0 
\par }{\b\f2\cgrid0 -What}{\f2\cgrid0 
\par :If the surrounding squares contain as many marks as the numbered square 
\par  predicts then the area is eligible for auto opening
\par 
\par }{\b\f2\cgrid0 -HowTo}{\f2\cgrid0 
\par :Left click and hold on a square which has a number inside.
\par  Then hold the right button.
\par 
\par }{\b\f2\cgrid0 -Outcome}{\f2\cgrid0 
\par :This will cause all adjacent squares to turn either: 
\par  >Blue: Squares are marked or uneligible for auto opening
\par  >Red : Square is eligible for auto opening
\par  >None: Already open
\par 
\par }{\f2\fs24\cgrid0 \\-----------\\
\par |The Options|>
\par /-----------/}{\f2\cgrid0 
\par 
\par }{\b\f2\cgrid0 -Pause/Unpause}{\f2\cgrid0 
\par  Pauses or Unpauses the game.
\par  Pressing p or the pause button will also work.
\par 
\par }{\b\f2\cgrid0 -Backgrounds}{\f2\cgrid0 
\par  When checked a random picture will appear under the board,
\par  if not checked a gray color will appear under revealed squares.
\par 
\par }{\b\f2\cgrid0 -Difficulty}{\f2\cgrid0 
\par 
\par  Easy:    1 Bomb for every 9 squares
\par           Time = (5 * # of bombs)
\par 
\par  Medium:  1 Bomb for every 8 squares
\par           Time = (4 * # of bombs)
\par 
\par  Hard:    1 Bomb for every 7 squares
\par           Time = (2 * # of bombs)
\par 
\par  Insane:  1 Bomb for every 6 squares
\par           Time = (1 * # of bombs)
\par 
\par 
